				\begin{document}$$error\,rate=\frac{1}{n}\sum _{i=1}^{n}\frac{{\sum }_{j=1}^{m}\,(1-pIB{S}_{ij})}{m}$$\end{document}errorrate=1n∑i=1n∑j=1m(1−pIBSij)mwhere, n is the number of accessions with biological replicates, pIBSij is the percent IBS for ith accession with its jth replicate, and m is the number of replicates for a given accession.
